Source: libcjwt
Version: 2.3.0
Upstream-URL: https://github.com/xmidt-org/cjwt.git
Upstream-Ref: 2586a5ea4594f75fe5958c88acfdd7a7f635a067
Build-Depends: libssl-dev, libcjson-dev, libtrower-base64

Package: libcjwt
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: C JWT implementation - runtime
 cjwt is a small JWT handler designed to allow consumers of JWTs of the
 JWS variant the ability to securely and easily get claims and data from
 a JWT. This particular JWT implementation uses cJSON and supports multiple
 different crypto libraries.
 .
 It provides secure JWT validation, claim extraction, and JWT creation
 capabilities with support for various signing algorithms.
 .
 This package contains the runtime library.

Package: libcjwt-dev
Section: libdevel
Priority: optional
Depends: libcjwt (= ${version})
Description: C JWT implementation - development files
 cjwt is a small JWT handler designed to allow consumers of JWTs of the
 JWS variant the ability to securely and easily get claims and data from
 a JWT.
 .
 This package contains headers and development files.
